<StalingradDeBr> <Generaloberst Paulus' 6th Army is advancing on Stalingrad. We have crossed the Tchir and are heading towards the very important industrial City on the Volga. Stalingrad is important not only because of its industry, but also because it is the gate to the Caucasus. By taking it, Heeresgruppe Sd can sever the connection between the oil fields of the Caucasus and the rest of the Soviet Union. The Battle of Stalingrad may decide the whole war! Luftflotte 4 has been severely strengthened by Fliegerkorps X that had been pulled back from Sicily. The Russians know of the importance of this battle as well and both the army and the air force have been strengthened severely. The Luftwaffe will have to do its utmost to support the drive of the 6th Army in this very important battle. >
<StalingradDeDb> <The 6th Army has taken the major part of Stalingrad and has crossed the Volga at several points. Luftflotte 4 has been instrumental in this struggle. The VVS has been up in strength as never before on the southern front, with new types and much more aggressive than ever. Nevertheless, the fighters of the Luftwaffe have gained control in the air and inflicted heavy losses at a relatively light cost. Troubling us is the weather situation, which is becoming increasingly worse in the last days. If this continues, we will not be able to fly in a few days and our troops will not be able to advance further without air cover.>
<StalingradRuBr> <The Germans are advancing on Stalingrad! Stavka has transferred every air unit at hand to the Volga front. The City must not fall, because that would sever the connection between the Caucasus and the rest of the USSR, stopping our indigenous oil supply and leaving us at the mercy of oil from the western allies. To prevent that, strong forces have been allocated to this sector. The VVS, equipped with new types and with the experience gained in the struggles of over a year, will try to claim air superiority. Stalingrad must not fall!>
<StalingradRuDb> <At the beginning of October, the German advance has been almost stopped. While the Germans control a major part of Stalingrad, every inch is costing them dearly and our forces are becoming stronger day by day. Soon we will launch a counteroffensive and drive them back!>
<StalingradHDeBr> <Generaloberst Paulus' 6th Army is advancing on Stalingrad. We have crossed the Tchir and are heading towards the very important industrial City on the Volga. Stalingrad is important not only because of its industry, but also because it is the gate to the Caucasus. By taking it, Heeresgruppe Sd can sever the connection between the oil fields of the Caucasus and the rest of the Soviet Union. The Battle of Stalingrad may decide the whole war! Luftflotte 4 has been severely strengthened by Fliegerkorps X that had been pulled back from Sicily. The Russians know of the importance of this battle as well and both the army and the air force have been strengthened severely. The Luftwaffe will have to do its utmost to support the drive of the 6th Army in this very important battle. >
