<Stalingrad2DeBr> <We have a serious situation at the Stalingrad front. The Russians have used to past November days of bad weather to launch a pincer operation at the flanks of the 6th army covered by Rumanian units. Both the northern and southern attacks have been completely devastating, totally scattering our front and throwing our entire rear area into total chaos. As you know well, several field bases of the Luftwaffe were overrun in the last days. The Soviets have trapped almost the entire 6th Army in a pocket around Stalingrad. The Staff of Luftflotte 4 and Panzergruppe Hoth are desperately trying to form a holding front made up mostly of scratch units formed from rear echelons and Luftwaffe ground personnel. At the same time, High command has ordered the Luftwaffe to resupply the 6th army, which is to remain at Stalingrad in order to bind Soviet forces. Oberst Dr. Khl, the Commodore of KG55, has been tasked with the coordination of the air effort to help Stalingrad. But with bad weather, a rear area in total confusion, our main airbases  under constant threat of being overrun, a precarious supply situation and the Soviet air force stronger than ever this task will be extremely difficult.>
<Stalingrad2DeDb> <It is over. On the 2nd February, the 6th Army capitulated. 200.000 German soldiers have been killed or captured. The Luftwaffe has given all it had, but it wasn't enough. The airlift alone cost 488 planes, an entire Fliegerkorps! But without Luftflotte 4, the situation would have been much worse. The Luftwaffe attacked advancing troops, protected the airfields in the pocket and often had to defend its own airfields. Heeresgruppe Sd will have to pull back to the Don front, except for the Kuban bridgehead, which will most likely have to be evacuated as well. For the first time in this war, we have suffered a total defeat. An uncertain future lies ahead of all of us.>
<Stalingrad2RuBr> <Operation Uranus, the Pincer movement against Kalach, was a huge success. The German 6th Army is now trapped in Stalingrad. For unknown reasons, the Germans have not yet attempted to break out of the pocket. We now have a unique opportunity at hand: To destroy an entire German field army and blunt the German war effort for the entire East front! As they did at Demyansk and Kholm in the northern sector, the Germans will most likely try to supply the 6th army from the air. The VVS will try to interdict the supply effort both by attacking airbases and shooting down transports in the air.>
<Stalingrad2RuDb> <In 2nd February 1943, the German 6th Army under command of Generaloberst Paulus capitulated. Over 200.000 half starved German and Rumanian soldiers have been taken prisoner. The terrible conditions in Stalingrad bear witness to how effective the efforts of the VVS against the air supply operations have been. This has been our greatest victory yet. Even more, the whole German front has been pushed back until almost the starting point of last year's German summer offensive. The German front is that weak that it might be possible to break through at Kharkov and liberate the entire Ukraine!>
