<Sychevka42DeBr> <Despite the losses of the severe winter of 1941 the Wehrmacht have managed to establish a stable defensive position in the Rzhev salient threatening Moscow.  The Soviets have built up large troop concentrations between this salient and Moscow, and unless they transfer their armies south to defend the Caucasus we can expect an attack.>
<Sychevka42DeDb> <The Soviets succeeded capturing an area west of Rzhev, but the main goals of their offensive were not accomplished before their commanders were transferred south.  We have had to reinforce the salient, which has left our forces in the south short of troops to guard their flanks, but in the August battles the Soviets have taken heavy losses for little gain.>
<Sychevka42RuBr> <After the difficult winter battles of early 1942, the central front before Moscow is still the critical sector. The Germans have thrown their forces into the advance in the south, while we have been gathering strength.  An offensive aimed at the northeast front of this salient will allow us to push the fascists further from Moscow and gain much-needed experience in the control of combined armoured-air operations. The VVS is to keep the front clear of Luftwaffe aircraft so that our bombers can make accurate attacks on enemy strongpoints and our tanks can be concentrated into attack formations.>
<Sychevka42RuDb> <Our offensive captured further territory from the fascist invader and diverted reserves away from the breakthrough in the south, though the cost was high.  The VVS has made further advances during this operation but we need to improve further if we are to contest the skies with the fascists.  The tactics of our armoured forces also need improving.>
