<Zhukov42SDeDb> <The Soviets succeeded in throwing back Heeresgruppe Mitte further, but the main goal, trapping large forces of it in a huge pocket west of Vyasma has not been accomplished. The scratch formation, Gefechtsverband Schmidt, kept constant pressure on the Soviets. The new Fw 190s have proven themselves to be very suited for East front conditions.>
<Zhukov42SRuBr> <After the difficult battles of summer 1942, the central front before Moscow remained quiet. The Germans threw all their forces in the advance in the south, while we were gathering strength. The frontline gives us the opportunity to try a pincer operation southward from the bulge at Rzhew in an attempt to isolate and destroy most of the German forces on the Moscow front, an accompanying operation to the one being mounted at Stalingrad, though we have been delayed by bad weather. Our southern armies are far from German territory: it is in the north that the fascists must be beaten.  In order for our offensive to succeed, the VVS must wrestle air superiority from the Germans and enable our troops to operate without a threat from German bombers.>
<Zhukov42SRuDb> <Our attacks south of Rzhev were not able to complete the isolation of the German occupiers and the attacks made further west did not even threaten an encirclement.  The strategic goal of our offensive was not met and the operation must be counted a failure, though it did prevent the fascists using their best troops to reinforce the weak armies of their allies in the south. The VVS has once again proven itself. Our fighters managed to master air combat against the new German fighters, while our ground attackers were more efficient than ever in supporting our troops.>
