<Orel43RuBr> <We have recaptured the city of Kursk, but our offensive is suffering from a lack of supplies and fresh troops.  However, the German armies are in similar difficulties and if we continue we may be able to encircle not only their Orel forces but also the armies in the salient west of Moscow. Partisan units have cut the supply lines to Orel and the road to Bryansk is only defended by small numbers of Hungarian troops.>
<Orel43RuDb> <Our armies almost recaptured Bryansk, but the German withdrawal from Rzhev meant that large numbers of reinforcements were available to them, and our successes could not be sustained.  With the retreat from Kharkov more divisions were needed in the south and we were unable to accomplish the more limited objective of surrounding Orel.  The rains have given us time to build up our forces.  The next large operation to recapture Orel will most likely take place in summer.>
