<Myskhako43RuBr> <Though the operations mounted by the Don front were successful, the objective of trapping German forces in the Crimea was not achieved.  Also, the Germans still have extensive defences covering Taman and bridgeheads over the Kuban River. The Red Army and Navy have established a beachhead at Myskhako to threaten the German lines from the south, and this will be combined with a new offensive in the centre. A fast operation is necessary, as we want to eliminate the Germans before they can be evacuated to the Crimea. Intelligence has been presented that the Germans will move strong air forces into the area in order to support their troops in an offensive against our positions. The battle will be a good opportunity to test the renewed tactics, pilots and planes of the VVS.> 
<Myskhako43RuDb> <For the very first time, the VVS met a strong Luftwaffe concentration head on and performed extremely well. Our new tactics have proven to be very effective at denying the Germans the ability to strike our troops, though we have yet to achieve enough superiority to be able to mount offensive missions against defended targets.  Also, the fascists were unable to wear our squadrons down and remained outnumbered at the end of the fighting.  If the German summer offensive is mounted in this sector we will be prepared for it, despite the failure to crush the bridgeheads over the Kuban river.  However, intelligence reports suggest that the next battle will centre on the salient around Kursk.>
