<Kuban43DeBr> <Things are beginning to look a little brighter again in the southern area: General von Manstein managed to blunt the Soviet advance at Kharkov with a series of bold manoeuvre battles, stabilizing the front. This ended the possibility of a "Super-Stalingrad" in the entire Crimea, Kuban and southern Ukraine. While the front is relatively stable in the Ukraine, Stalin apparently decided to try smaller bites first. Forces of Heeresgruppe Sd are still holding a chunk of the Soviet Kuban coast from Taman to Novorossisk. Intelligence indicates the Red Army will launch its next offensive exactly there. For that reason, the major part of Luftflotte 4, including the whole Jagdgeschwader 52, have been sent to airfields in the Kuban and Eastern Crimea. They will try to support the bridgehead against the Soviet onslaught. Since the flying weather is good, I am confident we will be able to achieve air supremacy. It is known the Soviet air force has moved very strong units there, mainly equipped with planes delivered from the Americans or British.>
<Kuban43DeDb> <The Soviets have failed to crush the Kuban bridgehead, but it was a close call. They managed to retake about half of the bridgehead and we will be forced to abandon it to avoid losing the troops holding it. The really worrying news is the extremely tough air battles that were fought over the Kuban. The Soviet air force, especially the fighters, was very well organized, numerically superior and very aggressive. The aces of JG 3 and 52 managed to hold themselves, but the air war over the East front is not what it used to be just half a year ago. The air war of the East front is becoming more and more unfavourable for our side.>
<Kuban43RuBr> <Even after our successful operation in the Don front area, the Germans still hold the Crimea and a bridgehead at the Kuban coast. The Red Army will eliminate this beachhead, liberating the coast from Krasnodar to Taman. A fast operation is necessary, as we want to deny the Germans the possibility of evacuation their forces to the Crimea. It can be assumed the Germans will move strong air forces into the bridgehead in order to support their troops. We have build up the VVS in this area as well. The battle will be a good opportunity to test new tactics and planes.>
<Kuban43RuDb> <Our troops have managed to liberate Krasnodar and a good part of the Kuban coast. More importantly, the VVS performed extremely well. For the very first time, the VVS met a strong Luftwaffe concentration head on and came out victorious. Our new tactics have proved to be very effective. While the German Kuban bridgehead has not been totally eliminated, the Germans will have to evacuate it in order to avoid greater losses. The frontlines are now set for a decision this summer.>
