<Kursk43SRuDb> <The German offensive began in July, but was slowed down by the deep minefields we had prepared. Even though the German army used its most modern tanks, their advance did not get far in face of the heroic resistance of our Red Army soldiers. While the VVS failed to destroy the Luftwaffe forces on the ground, it managed to claim air superiority in hard fought air battles, while our attack squadrons wiped out entire tank divisions! For the first time, we blunted a German offensive from the start, and by the second week our forces had taken the initiative from them and forced the evacuation of Orel.  This may well be the turning point of the war!>
<Kursk43HRuBr> <After this year's winter offensives, our forces have occupied a huge bulge in the front around Kursk. It is obvious the German leadership plans an attack on this bulge as the starting point for their summer offensive this year. For reasons unknown to us, however, this offensive has been delayed for almost two months now. This gave us the possibility to strengthen our forces in the Kursk bulge to a point where an attack cannot succeed. We expect the German forces to attack anyway, though. The task of our Air army will be to support the defence against the southern German pincer. Our main task will be to secure air supremacy and to attack German tanks and supply columns.>
