<ProkhorovkaDeBr> <After difficult defensive winter battles in the Ukraine, the frontlines have stabilized themselves again in April 1943. A significant Soviet bulge had developed at Kursk, followed by a German Bulge, the Orelbogen, north of it. At the time, the German high command had decided to crush this bulge in a pincer operation from north and south. The most modern equipment, including new heavy tanks will be brought up to support the offensive. The operation has already been delayed twice and Soviet forces in the bulge are very strong and fortified. Luftflotte 6 will support the southern Thrust. Main tasks will include winning air supremacy, close support and raids against the Soviet supply system.>
<ProkhorovkaDeDb> <Our offensive at Kursk met extremely heavy resistance. The advance bogged down after only a few kilometers due to heavy fortifications and strong counterattacks. The Soviets have had terrible losses but continue to throw more and more tanks at our poor soldiers. Luftflotte 4 gave an excellent performance against a very strong Soviet air force.  And even more important, our Stukas and Schlachtflieger managed to locate and destroy a Soviet brigade trying to envelop our northern thrust. The efforts of our Pilots alone turned a total defeat into a bloody draw. But the Orelbogen cannot be hold anymore, we will have to abandon it. For the first time, a major German summer offensive has failed.>
<ProkhorovkaHuBr> <After difficult defensive winter battles in the Ukraine, the frontlines have stabilized themselves again in April 1943. A significant Soviet bulge had developed at Kursk, followed by a German Bulge, the Orelbogen, north of it. At the time, the German high command had decided to crush this bulge in a pincer operation from north and south. The most modern equipment, including new heavy tanks will be brought up to support the offensive. The operation has already been delayed twice and Soviet forces in the bulge are very strong and fortified. The fighter units of the Royal Hungarian air force are attached to Luftflotte 6 and will support the southern Thrust. The main task is the protection of our ground forces from enemy bombers.>
<ProkhorovkaHuDb> <The German offensive at Kursk has failed, but our pilots have fought bravely and have shot down a huge number of Soviet planes. Unfortunately, American heavy bombers have started to raid Budapest and all fighter units are needed for home defence. It is bitter to leave our German comrades, but we have to.>
<ProkhorovkaRuBr> <After this year's winter offensives, our forces have occupied a huge bulge in the front around Kursk. It is obvious the German leadership plans an attack on this bulge as the starting point for their summer offensive this year. For reasons unknown to us, however, this offensive has been delayed for almost two months now. This gave us the possibility the strengthen our forces in the Kursk bulge to a point an attack cannot succeed. We expect the German forces to attack anyway, though. The task of our Air army will be to support the defence against the southern German pincer. Our main task will be to secure air supremacy and to attack German tanks and supply columns.>
<ProkhorovkaRuDb> <The German offensive starting in June became a total disaster for the Germans. Even though the German army used its most modern tanks, their advance did not get far in face of the heroic resistance of our Red Army soldiers. While the VVS failed to destroy the Luftwaffe forces on the ground, it managed to claim air superiority in hard fought air battles, while our attack squadrons wiped out entire tank divisions! For the first time, we blunted a German offensive from the start. This may well be the turning point of the war!>

<Kubanlate43DeBr> <After the failed Operation Zitadelle, the Russians have launched an offensive in the entire Ukraine. The Crimea is about to be cut off and in the Ukraine, Feldmarschall von Manstein has ordered the Army Group South to retreat behind the Dnjepr. The Kuban Bridgehead is totally isolated, and the 17th Army has to be evacuated. High Command has ordered the evacuation by sea to the Crimea, which is also threatened. The Luftwaffe has to protect the Evacuation with the meager remaining forces after the losses from Kursk. We are numerically inferior, but the fighting spirit of our fighter units is unbroken. Heavy resistance in the air and a massive sortie from the Black Sea fleet have to be expected.>
<Kubanlate43DeDb> <The last German soldier has left the Asiatic continent on the 9th October, when Taman was evacuated. The operation went along as planned with remarkably low losses, due to the heroic efforts of our Luftwaffe. The fighters of JG 52 have retained air supremacy and the Stukas managed to sink three Soviet destroyers and dealt a crippling blow to the Black Sea fleet.>
<Kubanlate43RuBr> <After the German offensive at Kursk has failed, the red army has launched a liberating offensive in the entire Ukraine! The German forces are fleeing to the Dniepr river line. Now it is time to eradicate the last german stronghold on the Caucasus, the Kuban bridgehead. The german 17th Army there could, if successfully evacuated, strengthen the german defense in the Crimea or the Ukraine. According to intelligence, the germans will this time not attempt to hold the bridgehead, but will evacuate. Thus, the main task of the VVS will be to interdict the evacuation of men and material across the straits of Kerch. The black Sea fleet will use all its remaining ships to support that operation. The german air units are still weakened from Kursk, while our equipment, training and moral are better than ever!>
<Kubanlate43RuDb> <The Red Banner is flying again over Taman! On the 9th October, the last German has left the Caucasus. Parts of the 17th Army managed to escape, though mostly without material. Also, they are now trapped on the Crimea. The VVS managed to sink a lot of transports, though the Black Sea fleet did not perform as expected and suffered heavy losses. The liberation of the Crimea is next!>

<Kutusov43DeBr> <The armoured reserves which were built up after Stalingrad have been squandered in the Kursk fighting and we are unable to restore our lines by rapid counterattack, as in the past.  If the Soviets are able to break our front between Vitebsk and Mogilev we will be forced to retreat once more.  It will be difficult for them to advance over territory that we have put to the fire, however, and our air forces should be able to take advantage by attacking their slow-moving columns.>
<Kutusov43DeDb> <Despite a severe lack of panzers, our infantry and artillery have managed to fight the Soviets to a standstill in this sector and their offensive has ended.  The Luftwaffe contributed by hindering the movement of Soviet armies to the front, though the escalating Allied air offensive over the Reich means that increasing numbers of our fighters and pilots are now being withdrawn to the west.>
<Kutusov43RuBr> <Our armies recaptured Smolensk in late September.  The buildings were set alight by the fascists before they withdrew and most of the old city has been destroyed.  Their armies are to be pursued and prevented from retreating into the fortifications they have established between Vitebsk and Mogilev.  If we defeat them here they have no natural line of defence remaining to them before the Soviet border.  Our task will then be to harass the enemy as they flee.>
<Kutusov43RuDb> <The weather prevented us from making a successful assault on the fascist strongpoints, though we were able to outflank Vitebsk from the north, taking Gorodok in November after a series of damp battles.  The offensive which began after the Kursk fighting has now run its course, and we are going to build up our forces for another onslaught next summer.>
