<Lvov44DeBr> <After the disaster around Smolensk and Vitebsk, the remains of Heeresgruppe Mitte are on constant retreat. A holding line has been set up around Lemberg in the southern part of the Soviet advance, but it will not hold very long. We expect the Soviet advance to turn south there and cross the Karpathian Mountains into Hungary. This move would cut off Germany from the oil fields in Rumania and Hungary. Heeresgruppe Sd will support the Royal Hungarian army in the defence of the Hungarian border. Luftflotte 6, supported by units of the RLV, will give air cover alongside the Hungarian air force.>
<Lvov44DeDb> <Lemberg fell after a short time, and the Soviets managed to cross the Carpathians into Hungary. At least we were able to prevent the Hungarians from changing sides. While the Luftwaffe and the Hungarian air force fought well, they were simply overwhelmed by the Soviets.>
<Lvov44RuBr> <After crushing the enemy front in Belarus, our forces are moving westward very quickly. The next target of the Red Army's advance is Lvov. From this city, several armies will turn south and try to force their way over the Carpathian Mountains into Hungary, Debrecen being the first target. The taking of large parts of Hungary will sever the German access to the oil fields of Rumania and Hungary. For that reason, heavy resistance from both Hungarian and German forces can be expected.>
<Lvov44RuDb> <The Red Army successfully took Lvov and managed to cross the Dukla pass over the Carpathians into Hungary. A Hungarian attempt to negotiate a separate peace was crushed by the Germans, turning a satellite state into another occupied country. The Hungarian military however fights on. Once again, the VVS was very successful in supporting the advance and gained air supremacy over both Hungarian and German enemies.>
<Lvov44HuBr> <After the Soviets crushed the German central front, they are in a position to attack Hungary from the north. Even though the Americans heavily bomb Budapest and other cities, the defence of our borders is more important. All available MHKL squadrons will support the defensive battles in the Carpathians.>
<Lvov44HuDb> <The Soviets managed to break into Hungarian territory, despite our and the Luftwaffe's best efforts. A small clique of aristocrats tried to negotiate a separate peace, but the Hungarian military will fight on alongside our German comrades in arms.>

