<BalatonDeBr> <Soviet forces surrounded Budapest in February and took it after brutal house fighting. Now, in March, the frontline is just along the southeastern shore of the Plattensee. 1st SS Panzerkorps has been brought up to the front and will launch an offensive aimed at liberating Budapest. Luftflotte 4 and the Hungarian air force will support the Operation Frhlingserwachen. Most important tasks will be close support and escort for our jabos.>
<BalatonDeDb> <Operation Frhlingserwachen didn't get far. Due to mud and rain, the offensive bogged down after a few kilometres and the SS units had to withdraw in order not to get enveloped. A few days later, the Soviets launched their own offensive. Our forces were unable to stop them and by mid April the Soviets crossed the Austrian border and took Vien. Luftflotte 4 and our Hungarian brothers in arms fought bravely, shooting down a large number of Soviet planes. But Soviet and American superiority in numbers was too large to let us make a difference. A few days after Wien, Berlin fell as well. The war is over, and all Luftwaffe units are ordered to fly westward and surrender themselves to the Americans. At least most of us will have a country to return to, unlike our Hungarian comrades. You fought well, all we fought for was in vain.>
<BalatonRuBr> <While our central fronts are converging on Berlin, the Red Army managed to take Budapest, the capital of Germany's last ally. Now in March 1945 the frontline is around lake Balaton and the army is ready to strike further into Austria. The VVS will support this offensive aimed at liberating Austria from German occupation.>
<BalatonRuDb> <The German SS launched a rather weak offensive in mid March, which did not penetrate very far. Immediately afterwards, our own offensive began, quickly sweeping the Germans from Hungary into Austria. Vienna was taken in May, and the triumph of the southern fronts is as complete as the victory at Berlin. The VVS fought brilliantly against the Luftwaffe's last gasp and came out victorious again. Our complete victory over fascism was to a large part due to the VVS.>
<BalatonHuBr> <Budapest has fallen after a brutal battle, and the Soviets have conquered most of our country. Still, we have to do our duty as soldiers of the Royal Hungarian army. We will fight alongside the Luftwaffe until the last man. Yet, there is hope: the German elite 1. SS Panzerkorps will launch an offensive to liberate Budapest. I expect all of you to give your utmost in this desperate battle.>
<BalatonHuDb> <The offensive of the SS has failed after a few days and the Soviets have pushed the Germans back to the Austrian border. Sopron was the last Hungarian city to fall into their hands. Our country is again in the hands of the Bolsheviks and the Red terror of 1919 will return. At least we have shown the world how royal Hungarian soldiers fight and have done our duty. But our country is lost for us and we will have to go into exile.>
