<BalatonTLDRFWinterRuBr> <Lake Balaton: the 1st bitter months of the end. While our central fronts are converging on Berlin, the Red Army managed to take Budapest, the capital of Germany's last ally. Now in March 1945 the frontline is around lake Balaton and the army is ready to strike further into Austria. The VVS will support this offensive aimed at liberating Austria from German occupation.>
<BalatonTLDRFRuBr> <Lake Balaton last war month.>
<BalatonTLDRFWinterRuDb> < >
<BalatonTLDRFRuDb> <The German SS launched a rather weak offensive in mid March, which did not penetrate very far. Immediately afterwards, our own offensive began, quickly sweeping the Germans from Hungary into Austria. Vienna was taken in May, and the triumph of the southern fronts is as complete as the victory at Berlin. The VVS fought brilliantly against the Luftwaffe's last gasp and came out victorious again. Our complete victory over fascism was to a large part due to the VVS.>

